Explanation:

The problem requires finding the number of ways to roll the dice to get a sum equal to the target. We can use a simple loop to iterate from 1 to the target value and multiply the number of dice (n) with the number of faces (k) for each die. Since the result is always less than 10^9 + 7, we can directly calculate the result without any additional operations.

